	<text>
		<body>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Louisville Ky</placeName> <date>18 July. 5614</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
				<p>Rev Sir&#44;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;In page 230 of No 4 Vol 12 of the Occident&#44;<lb/> appears an article headed <placeName>Louisville</placeName>&#44; the <date>5<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date> line of which<lb/> contains the following words&#58;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">&#8220;it may suffer for a while from unfaithful leaders&#59;&#8221;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">As I am a candidate for the office&#44; and as it<lb/> has been hinted by rivals &#38;c. that the above is<lb/> intended to apply to me&#44; I would respectfully<lb/> ask you either privately or in your public capacity<lb/> as Editor&#44; to state whether such construction<lb/> is intended thereby and if so&#44; on what grounds<lb/> such assertion is founded.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I may be permitted to add that <hi rend="underline">I</hi><lb/> had no conception of so construing your language&#59;<lb/> but am induced to address you in consequence<lb/> of the interpretation of others.</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)">Entreating an early reply&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)">I am</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)">Rev Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)">respectfully Yours</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author">A. J. H. Bernal</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(8)"><placeName>226 Green St</placeName></p>
			
